main event: A UFO report from Genessee Mt., Colorado on October 28, 1950 with 2 photos.
interesting points: The photos depict indistinct circular or spherical shapes with unclear details, possibly indicating unidentified flying objects.
The images show grainy and speckled backgrounds, making it difficult to identify specific details.
There are handwritten marks or annotations on one of the photographs, potentially labeling objects or areas within the photo.
The photographs were part of an unclassified document, likely indicating government interest in the sightings.
The report was downgraded at 3-year intervals and declassified after 12 years, as per DOD DIR 5200.10.
